On Jun 13, 2007, at 10:13 AM, Mike Soultanian wrote:

> The part I don't get is where they get the ground to complete the  
> circuit that powers the unit, which would also be the same ground  
> used to ground the the negative side of the coil.  Do they use the  
> distributor as a ground?  I never really looked at my unit when I  
> installed it so I'm curious if it's grounding through the  
> installation screw...

Yes. The plastic modules are usually mounted on a metal plate which  
is defacto grounded to the engine through the distributor's advance  
plate and that braided wire inside.

